Have you ever stopped to think that your brain has been wired over the milennia to equate saying &quot;who is the man&quot; to yourself with practicing? Or if not practicing at least fooling yourself into thinking maybe I can make a child.<br>
<br>
We've left the realm of thinking here, Halo. It's biology and it's a lot harder to break away from than you might want to believe. I'd even go so far as to offer that homosexual urges originate with the very same urges that lead people to want to procreate. You could go so far as to say that homosexuality, in particular male homosexuality is the urge to procreate gone too far. It's fairly well established that the gate-keeper effect of women on sexual frequency is negated when considering men. Not 100% negated but it's there. Now if the biological urge is the act of sex and not a cognitive process of performing sex where the person actively acknowledges the likelihood of conception occurring, then it's not all surprising that we should see the sex drive alive and well if not more pervasive than ever in both the homosexual and heterosexual communities. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36323">Caean Sacroguerre, Knight of Tunare</a>
